If you don't have people on who can kill Gorenaire, then your problem is not with MB teams, your problem is simply that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> anyone</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> wants to kill Gore.<br>
<br>
If you have people on, but they're all doing their own thing rather than formed up in guild groups who can port when needed, then your problem is either with guild organization/cohesiveness, or that your guild just doesn't consider your epic worth the effort.<br>
<br>
<br>
Guilds can respond faster for Gorenaire than they ever could for Ragefire. You only have to zone once (as opposed to 2 with a druid porter and 3 with a wiz porter), and you don't have to clear through trash mobs to get there. Seeing how people could respond to Ragefire in under 10 minutes, you should have a very good chance at killing Gore before the mana burn teams even know he's up! Whole guilds can mobilize for Gore nearly instantly (6 per porter online) if they so desire.<br>
