<br>
No, I don't think that.<br>
<br>
I think if you do the work <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> before</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Gore spawns that can be done before gore spawns, you can do it very fast.<br>
<br>
My example was of having 4 exp groups each with a porter who are prepared to port and kill gore given the word.<br>
<br>
Grouping? You already have 4 groups. And if you need to optimize groups, if you know what they have to look like before hand it's easy. E.G. 4 clerics disband and group, grab 2 MTs, and then the druids join up for healing the other groups. If you know beforehand you're gonna do this, it can be done very fast.<br>
<br>
Buffing? Everyone in those 4 groups should have symbol/BoF/HB (or aego) in their groups. Once the raid organizes, slap focus and sta on some MTs, a couple keis or group c2s, a few SoS's, and your raid has virtually every buff it needs in less than a minute. (not everyone on the raid <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> needs</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> full buffs; it's nice, but not a necessity)<br>
<br>
Organizing? Organization can be done before you port over and are all in one group over by the BW zone line. Make sure people know what to do while you're waiting instead of delaying it until the mob is up.<br>
<br>
Leading? Again, know what's going on beforehand rather than waiting until it's needed.<br>
<br>
Mobilization? 4 exp groups each with their porter can all meet up in DL in 5 minutes or less.<br>
<br>
<br>
But coming form another raid is a good idea, that I didn't think of. Go sit your guild in hate/fear/arena/HoT doing some armor farming, but organize the groups so they're ready to leave on a moment's notice to DL when Gore pops, or EJ for when Sev pops, etc. I.E. 1 porter per group, and let people know that's what's gonna happen and let them know what they're gonna do to the dragon while you're still sitting in your armor farming raid.<br>
<br>
