<br>
Do you think that 5 man insta-kill greed teams are what was envisioned for Manaburn?<br>
<br>
I don't...  no one &quot;deserves&quot; to be able to hold many other classes at ransom because they have the ability to insta-kill a mob of that caliber.<br>
<br>
ALL other combinations that any guild that would be killing said mobs for game progression would need a balanced reasonable raid of multiple groups.  Even a high end combo of classes of up to 6 would have risk in that the mob would get to defend itself...<br>
<br>
Sure, larger guilds sometimes need something, and they are welcome to try it with 5-6 people, but they would only rarely take one...  the fact of the matter is, team MB is so easy, so quick, and so efficient that 1-2-3-dead isnt even rare.<br>
<br>
<br>
Manaburn was likely designed to give Wizards a method to deliver their payload on ANY mob.  To make the the ultimate in reliable big punches.  I have absolutely no problem with that concept.<br>
<br>
Yes, I am talking about a nerf...  but not to the functionality... or to the damage... only to the range (down to 100) and the fact that ALL big punches would have a defense in both PvE and PvP in the form of a realtively common spell line (or lines).<br>
<br>
Would this stop wizards from delivering the big punch in a real raid?  No..... not if they have been raiding for any amount of time and know what aggro control is...<br>
<br>
The spellshield/rune/Xskin series stoping at least one full blow doesnt change jack for raids...  it just makes PvP more fun and makes for a magical defense and a way for melee to defend themselves against the one-hit wonders.  This actually makes it so a wizard who manaburns you down can say &quot;gotcha&quot; without a response &quot;well there is no defense for manaburn&quot;  it would take skill and strategy to land manaburn.<br>
<br>
Indeed, it even brings a real use for those spells on a raid and the cheesy mutliple HT- you are dead without a fight encounters.<br>
<br>
The game is no fun when the fight is over before it begins...  without challenge, there is no fun.  Think how long we would have played everquest if we started at level 60 with 500AAXP and all the best items in the game for your class.  You walk up to a mob and click the &quot;instakill&quot; button and it dies...<br>
yup real fun...  PvP would be a blast too... who can click faster...<br>
<br>
The problem with everquest is not that things are too powerful, its that there is no defense.<br>
<br>
