Well, we are at least heading in the same direction now. I don't think that the range of MB would fix the major sticking point people have with MB. There is actually a very simple way to get around the range thing when it comes to dragons. It takes a few hours but any player greedy enough to monopolize all the dragon spawns will take the time to do it.<br>
<br>
If you have good faction you can stand next to the dragon while you burn it. Now THAT is truly an instakill. Currently, there are just enough variable that there is about a 10% chance of death on a burn. If everyone burning has good faction, you have eliminated the pull and and factors related to it. Go kill the dorf king for a few hours and the dragons will love you.<br>
